    <main>
        <section class="hero" id="experience">
            <div class="container hero-grid">
                <div>
                    <h1>Foothills farm life with room to build and fly.</h1>
                    <p>Flying Changes Farm spans both sides of Pumpkintown Road in Marietta, South Carolina. Horses graze beside Houston and Kronk the goats, a private airstrip lifts Pinnacle Paramotor pilots, primitive campers unwind near the hangar, and code ships from the workshop office.</p>
                    <div class="hero-highlight">
                        <div class="hero-actions">
                            <a class="button" href="camp.html">Explore the campsite</a>
                            <a class="button" href="apps.html" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-sky), var(--color-forest));">See recent builds</a>
                        </div>
                        <div class="stat-card">
                            <strong>438 Pumpkintown Rd</strong>
                            <span>Marietta, SC 29661 · Blue Ridge foothills · multi-use acreage on both sides of the road.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="preview-image">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1473448912268-2022ce9509d8?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80" alt="Morning light across a South Carolina pasture with rolling hills">
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="container">
                <h2 class="section-title">Spaces on Pumpkintown Road</h2>
                <p class="section-subtitle">The property flexes between agriculture, aviation, camping, and technology. These are the main hubs visitors encounter.</p>
                <div class="feature-grid">
                    <article class="feature-card">
                        <h3>Pasture &amp; herd</h3>
                        <p>Rotational grazing keeps the hillside healthy for the horses and goats. Trails link the barns, fencing, and creek-side shade.</p>
                        <a href="horses.html">Animals &amp; care →</a>
                    </article>
                    <article class="feature-card">
                        <h3>Hangar &amp; runway</h3>
                        <p>Pinnacle Paramotor trains from the on-site airstrip. The hangar doubles as a lounge, workshop, and storm shelter during rebuilds.</p>
                        <a href="pinnacle.html">Flight overview →</a>
                    </article>
                    <article class="feature-card">
                        <h3>Primitive campsite</h3>
                        <p>Pitch a tent beside the pasture, gather around the fire pit, and use the hangar for bathroom access and rainy-day cover.</p>
                        <a href="camp.html">Campsite details →</a>
                    </article>
                    <article class="feature-card">
                        <h3>Workshop &amp; code</h3>
                        <p>Routing apps, caregiver scheduling tools, and recovery planning software are prototyped from the hangar office.</p>
                        <a href="apps.html">Build log →</a>
                    </article>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="container">
                <h2 class="section-title">Airfield snapshot</h2>
